 Vitaliy Vodolazskyy 123RF.com&#x201c;President Jacob Zuma has, in terms of section 26 (3) of the National Credit Act, 2005, appointed members to the National Consumer Tribunal (NCT) for a period of five years, effective from 1 July 2017 until 30 June 2022,&#x201d; said the Presidency on Wednesday, 21 June 2017. The President has appointed the following members to the National Consumer Tribunal: Prof Joseph Mandla Maseko (Executive Chairperson) Laura Anne Best (Deputy Chairperson) Lulama Andisa Potwana Diane Reinette Terblanche Adv Frans Kgolela Manamela Xolela Christopher May Penelope Anne Beck-Paxton Prof Tanya Woker Adv Hope Fiona Neo Sephoti Prof Bonke Clayton Dumisa Fungai Khumbulani Sibanda Nomfundo Sylvia Maseti Maleho Margaret Nkomo Prof Kasturi Moodaliyar Dr Maria Claudina Du Toit Lehlohonolo Lucky Rabotapi Trevor Albert Bailey</li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li>President Zuma congratulated all the members and wished them well in their new responsibilities. The National Consumer Tribunal, which is an independent adjudicative entity, was established in terms of the National Credit Act 34 of 2005 (the NCA). The Tribunal derives its mandate from the NCA and as such, hears all sides of a case before making a decision. A decision by the Tribunal has the same status as one made by a High Court.